@code{iSkeletonBone}
@end itemize

@subheading Skyboxes
@cindex @code{CS_ENTITY_CAMERA}

Meshes that use the @code{CS_ENTITY_CAMERA} flag no longer have to be placed
in a render priority that has the @samp{camera} flag set. This render
priority flag is no longer required (but @code{CS_ENTITY_CAMERA} still is!).

@subheading CS_FX_GOURAUD removed
@cindex @code{CS_FX_GOURAUD}

Gouraud is much more commonly used than flat shading and is thus the default 
now. To achieve the opposite behaviour (ie the behaviour when 
@code{CS_FX_GOURAUD} was not present), use the @code{CS_FX_FLAT} flag.

@subheading Collision Detection Changes
@cindex @sc{rapid}
@cindex @sc{opcode}
@cindex @code{iCollideSystem}

The most important change is that @sc{opcode} is now prefered over
@sc{rapid}. The @sc{opcode} plugin is free of restrictions (as opposed
to @sc{rapid} which can't be used in commercial programs), it is faster,
and uses a lot less memory. In future we will remove the @sc{rapid} plugin.

The @code{iCollideSystem::CollidePath()} utility method has been relocated to
@code{csColliderHelper::CollidePath()}. In addition there are a few extra
overloads that can make life easier for calculating collisions on a path.

@subheading Isometric Engine

The isometric engine has been removed.  It was beyond repair.  The
@samp{isotest} application remains, though, and demonstrates how you can
simulate an isometric look with the normal 3D engine.

